at the early modern period was a moment of transition in the configurations of the self, Sluhovsky offers a broad panorama of spiritual and devotional techniques of self-formation and subjectivation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aChristian life. 0aDevotional literaturexHistory and criticism. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aSociety of Jesus.  aSpiritual Exercises.  aself-formation.  asubjecthood.  asubjectivization.  atechniques.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226473048423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226473048/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles